				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Emotion makes ordinary people do extraordinary things. Combine that with the power of sport—“the one thing that can make the world put aside their differences and unite”— and you’ve got one heck of a story to tell.</p>
<p>If you’ve watched anything on NBC in the last 2-3 months, you’ve probably seen at least one of their advertisements for the Sochi Winter Olympic Games. Powerful is the only word I can use to describe them. As an avid sports fan, Olympic enthusiast, videographer, and former copywriter, I can honestly say these 30-second spots are some of the most compelling advertisements on TV today. Their messages are beautifully crafted and the visuals work so well with the inspiring voiceover—I only hope I can produce something like them some day.</p>
<p>Through these Sochi ads, NBC is telling a story that strikes a chord in every person who has ever had a dream. You don’t have to like sports to understand the appeal. I dare you to watch one of these ads and NOT get goosebumps…</p>
<p>Enjoy!</p>
